cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the task of predicting the 6D camera pose from a single RGB image in a given 3D environment, which is a problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions autonomous driving and augmented reality, which are related to robotics and control (cs.RO). The use of neural networks for learning the camera localization process suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with 3D scene geometry and surface regression, which could be related to computer graphics (cs.GR).
